The paper discusses the use of Linked Data technology for metadata enrichment in the computer science domain, which is relevant to several sub-categories. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper deals with bibliographic data. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) are also likely as they involve searching and retrieving information. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are less likely but still possible as they involve data analysis and discovery.
